chunks.text: ## MAXIMO SELF-PACED TRAINING GUIDE ## INFORMATION SECURITY OFFICER (ISO) TRAINING ## The Information Security Officer (ISO) Role in Maximo In Maximo, the Information Security Officer (ISO) uses the Service Request application to certify Asset(s) requiring sanitization prior to final approval by the Custodial Official and the Asset picked up the Personal Property Management (PPM). ## Available Training Resources User Guides, Job Aids and Quick Reference Documents are available on the EAWM Maximo Training Page to help users learn their role and responsibilities in Maximo at their own pace and in a mode that best fits their learning style. - · User Guides provide the greatest amount of detail on each topic. User Guides include a high-level summary, detailed step-by-step instructions with screen captures, and a Business Process Model mapping out the activities performed by each affected Functional Community. User Guides can be found in the 'Training Materials by Role' section of the Train

een captures, and a Business Process Model mapping out the activities performed by each affected Functional Community. User Guides can be found in the 'Training Materials by Role' section of the Training page, under via links to the Functional Community and Role name. - · Job Aids target critical functionality in Maximo. These documents are intended to be brief and focus on key issues, highlighting essential steps. These are found in the 'User Documentation' section of the Training page. - · Quick Reference Documents (QRDs) include step-by-step work instructions, in simplest terms. Unlike Job Aids and User Guides, QRDs normally do not include screen captures. These are also posted in the 'User Documentation' section. In addition to the items available on the Training page, this Self-Paced Training Guide directs you to short video demonstrations recorded and narrated by Maximo Instructors as they walk through the steps of completing specific tasks in Maximo.

To train for your role, read the appropriate User Guide, Job Aid and/or QRD for a given topic to gain an understanding of the process. Also, watch the video demonstrations as noted below. Continue reviewing this information until you are ready to start working in Maximo. IMPORTANT! Please DO NOT attempt to practice any of the steps in the Maximo Production system. If, after reviewing the materials, you are still uncomfortable with working in Maximo, contact your Maximo Site Lead for additional guidance. ## MAXIMO SELF-PACED TRAINING GUIDE ## Asset Turn-In and Sanitization The ISO certifies Turn-In Asset(s) requiring sanitization have been sanitized changes Status of the Service Request to move the process forward for final disposition of the Asset(s) using the Service Request application.
